The paper presents a graph-to-graph variational autoencoder that uses reinforcement learning to decode molecular graphs from latent embeddings. This involves techniques from machine learning (specifically, reinforcement learning and variational autoencoders) applied to molecular graphs. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.CL (Computation and Language), cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition), and cs.SD (Software Engineering).
